original: Carlsund, Herbert, lasarettsläkare, Uddevalla, f. 30/1/97 i Pajala, Norrb. 1’., alv pir o v idiäk. Herman Jöhanrs-isom o. Siigrid Cairlis’und. G. 35 m. Brita Söderbaum. Barn: Anne-Marie f. 37, Tony 39, Peter 42, Elisabet 45. — Stud:ex. i Uddevalla 15, med. kand. i Upps. 20, med. lic. i Sthlm 26. Assist :läk. v. Uddevalla las. 23, tf. andre und:läk. 24-26, assist :läk. v. Sabbatsb. sjukh. röntgenavd. 26-27, andre und:-läk. v. Uddevalla las. 27-28, förste dito där 28-29, und :läk. v. Sabbatsb. sjukh. röntgenavd. 29-32, las :läk. v. Uddevalla las. röntgenavd. sed. 32. Skr.: Bidr. t. röntgendiagnosen av främmande kroppar i matstrupen.
translated: Carlsund, Herbert, hospital physician, Uddevalla, born Jan 30th, 1897 in Pajala, Norrbotten county, son of Herman Johanneson and Sigrid Carlsund. Married in 1935 to Brita Söderbaum. Children: Anne-Marie born in 1937, Tony in 1939, Peter in 1942, Elisabet in 1945. Completed studies: graduated from high school in Uddevalla in 1915, received a Bachelor of Medicine in Uppsala in 1920, obtained a medical degree in Stockholm in 1926. Worked as an assistant physician at Uddevalla hospital in 1923, acting second assistant physician from 1924-1926, assistant physician at Sabbatsberg hospital's radiology department from 1926-1927, second assistant physician at Uddevalla hospital from 1927-1928, first assistant physician there from 1928-1929, assistant physician at Sabbatsberg hospital's radiology department from 1929-1932, and hospital physician at Uddevalla hospital's radiology department since 1932. Wrote: Contributions to the radiological diagnosis of foreign bodies in the esophagus.
